            <step1>
                <para count="1">Preheat frame rail along the weld joint to 500 to 600&#176;F (260 to 316&#176;C) to
                    insure any moisture present is eliminated and to prevent too rapid cooling of weld metal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Direct current, reversed polarity is preferred. Weld using a short arc and a beading or
                    narrow weave technique.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slag should be removed after each pass and an interpass temperature of 200&#176;F (93&#176;C)
                    should be maintained.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grind smooth and flush with surrounding sidemember material. Grind the weld in a
                    direction that is at 90&#176; to crack direction (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0100104">Figure 10D</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Add reinforcement.</para>
            </step1>
