        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Heat Treated Frames (110,000 PSI Yield Strength)</title>
            <para>When welding Heat Treated Frames (110,000 PSI Yield Strength), use low hydrogen electrodes which have
                superior crack resistance and notch toughness similar to AWS-E-11018. This type electrode should be
                stored in a moisture-free container to avoid porosity during welding.
            </para>
            <para>Amperage and voltage recommendations for welding are shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="t0100104">Table 4</hotlnk>.
            </para>
